<item>
            <title>[LU-1208] CATALOGS and lov_objid records are written and read in host byte orders</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1208</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Although I haven&apos;t verify this by looking into a target from a PPC server somewhere, the b1_8, master, and Orion code at the time of writing seems to write and read CATALOGS and lov_objid records in host byte orders.  This prevents users from starting, for example, targets created by PPC servers on x86_64 ones.  Also, a thorough search for similar bugs would be desirable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
